The paper proposes a novel end-to-end graph learning framework for jointly learning the graph structure and graph embeddings simultaneously. This falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The proposed framework also involves image data, which suggests that it could be relevant to the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of regularization and iterative methods, which are common techniques in optimization and signal processing, respectively, indicating that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.SI and cs.CL sub-categories.
